Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear shows a small area with the impression of wood, probably from a bolt or a box knob, roughly perpendicular to this an impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.30 cm. The front side is flat with finger impressions and shows part of an oval seal with a circumferential line. The motif shows part of a nfr, a Hm (U36), a possible nTr-flag and maybe a rDj (X8) on top of a nb-basket.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
